FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedListExecInstLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListExecInst (353) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedListExecInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListExecInst (69) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListExecInst field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedTextLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText (355) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text (58) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedSubjectLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSubject (357) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedSubject
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Subject (147) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Subject field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedHeadlineLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedHeadline (359) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedHeadline
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Headline (148) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Headline field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedAllocTextLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAllocText (361) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedAllocText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AllocText (161) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AllocText field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuerLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingIssuer (363) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuer
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingIssuer (306) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingIssuer field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDescLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc (365) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingSecurityDesc (307) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingSecurityeDesc field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Executed price for an AllocAccount (79) entry used when using “executed price” vs. “average price” allocations (e.g. Japan).

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteSetValidUntilTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates expiration time of this particular QuoteSet (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteEntryRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason Quote Entry was rejected: Valid values: 1 = Unknown symbol (Security) 2 = Exchange(Security) closed 3 = Quote exceeds limit 4 = Too late to enter 5 = Unknown Quote 6 = Duplicate Quote 7 = Invalid bid/ask spread 8 = Invalid price 9 = Not authorized to quote security 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastMsgSeqNumProcessed
FixFieldSpec.Description: The last MsgSeqNum (34) value received by the FIX engine and processed by downstream application, such as trading engine or order routing system. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefTagID
FixFieldSpec.Description: The tag number of the FIX field being referenced.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefMsgType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The MsgType (35) of the FIX message being referenced.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SessionRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify reason for a session-level Reject message. Valid values: 0 = Invalid tag number 1 = Required tag missing 2 = Tag not defined for this message type 3 = Undefined Tag 4 = Tag specified without a value 5 = Value is incorrect (out of range) for this tag 6 = Incorrect data format for value 7 = Decryption problem 8 = Signature problem 9 = CompID problem 10 = SendingTime accuracy problem 11 = Invalid MsgType 12 = XML Validation error 13 = Tag appears more than once 14 = Tag specified out of required order 15 = Repeating group fields out of order 16 = Incorrect NumInGroup count for repeating group 17 = Non “data” value includes field delimiter (SOH character) 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidRequestTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the Bid Request message type. Valid values: N = New C = Cancel

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraBroker
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies contra broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ComplianceID
FixFieldSpec.Description: ID used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

FixFieldSpec.Name: SolicitedFlag

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecRestatementReason

FixFieldSpec.Name: BusinessRejectRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: The value of the business-level “ID” field on the message being referenced.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BusinessRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject message. FixFieldSpec.Name: GrossTradeAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total amount traded (e.g. CumQty (14) * AvgPx (6)) expressed in units of currency.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoContraBrokers
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of ContraBroker (375) entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaxMessageSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Maximum number of bytes supported for a single message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoMsgTypes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of MsgTypes (35) in repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MsgDirection
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the direction of the messsage. Valid values: S = Send R = Receive

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoTradingSessions
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of TradingSessionIDs (336) in repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotalVolumeTraded

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClientBidID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a Bid Request as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListName

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoRelatedSym
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of securities. (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named TotalNumSecurities)

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the type of Bid Request. Valid values: 1 = “Non Disclosed” Style (e.g. US/European) 2 = “Disclosed” Style (e.g. Japanese) 3 = No Bidding Process

FixFieldSpec.Name: NumTickets

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideValue1
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amounts in currency

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideValue2
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amounts in currency

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoBidDescriptors
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of BidDescriptor (400) entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidDescriptorType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the type of BidDescriptor (400). Valid values: 1 = Sector 2 = Country 3 = Index

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidDescriptor
FixFieldSpec.Description: BidDescriptor value. Usage depends upon BidDescriptorTyp (399). If BidDescriptorType =1 Industrials etc - Free text If BidDescriptorType =2 "FR" etc - ISO Country Codes If BidDescriptorType =3 FT100, FT250, STOX - Free text

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideValueInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify which "SideValue" the value refers to. SideValue1 and SideValue2 are used as opposed to Buy or Sell so that the basket can be quoted either way as Buy or Sell. Valid values: 1 = SideValue1 2 = SideValue 2

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityPctLow
FixFieldSpec.Description: Liquidity indicator or lower limit if TotalNumSecurities (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityPctHigh
FixFieldSpec.Description: Upper liquidity indicator if TotalNumSecurities (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Value between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency

FixFieldSpec.Name: EFPTrackingError
FixFieldSpec.Description: Eg Used in EFP trades 12% (EFP – Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: FairValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used in EFP trades

FixFieldSpec.Name: OutsideIndexPct
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ValueOfFutures
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used in EFP trades

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityIndType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator. Valid values: 1 = 5day moving average 2 = 20 day moving average 3 = Normal Market Size 4 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: WtAverageLiquidity
FixFieldSpec.Description: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExchangeForPhysical
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical. Valid values: Y = True N = False

FixFieldSpec.Name: OutMainCntryUIndex
FixFieldSpec.Description: Value of stocks in Currency

FixFieldSpec.Name: CrossPercent
FixFieldSpec.Description: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ProgRptReqs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports. Valid values: 1 = BuySide explicitly requests status using StatusRequest (Default) The sell-side firm can however, send a DONE status List Status Response in an unsolicited fashion 2 = SellSide periodically sends status using ListStatus. Period optionally specified in ProgressPeriod 3 = Real-time execution reports (to be discouraged)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ProgPeriodInterval
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means don’t send status.

FixFieldSpec.Name: IncTaxInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross. Valid values: 1 = Net 2 = Gross

FixFieldSpec.Name: NumBidders
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidTradeType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the type of trade. Valid values: R = Risk Trade G = VWAP Guarantee A = Agency J = Guaranteed Close (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named "TradeType")

FixFieldSpec.Name: BasisPxType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the basis price type. Valid values: 2 = Closing Price at morning session 3 = Closing Price 4 = Current price 5 = SQ 6 = VWAP through a day 7 = VWAP through a morning session 8 = VWAP through an afternoon session 9 = VWAP through a day except "YORI" (an opening auction) A = VWAP through a morning session except "YORI" (an opening auction) B = VWAP through an afternoon session except "YORI" (an opening auction) C = Strike D = Open Z = Others

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoBidComponents
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the number of list entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Country
FixFieldSpec.Description: ISO Country Code in field

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoStrikes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes (428) in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID (66). Used to support fragmentation.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the price type. Valid values: 1 = Percentage (e.g. percent of par) (often called "dollar price" for fixed income) 2 = Per unit (i.e. per share or contract) 3 = Fixed Amount (absolute value) 4 = Discount – percentage points below par 5 = Premium – percentage points over par 6 = Spread 7 = TED price 8 = TED yield 9 = Yield 10 = Fixed cabinet trade price (primarily for listed futures and options) 11 = Variable cabinet trade price (primarily for listed futures and options) (For Financing transactions PriceType implies the “repo type” – Fixed or Floating – 9 (Yield) or 6 (Spread) respectively - and Price (44) gives the corresponding “repo rate”. See Volume 1: "Glossary" for further value definitions)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DayOrderQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: For GT orders, the OrderQty (38) less all quantity (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty (424) = OrderQty – (CumQty (14) – DayCumQty (425))

FixFieldSpec.Name: DayCumQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DayAvgPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: The average price for quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

FixFieldSpec.Name: GTBookingInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate. Valid values: 0 = book out all trades on day of execution 1 = accumulate executions until order is filled or expires 2 = accumulate until verbally notified otherwise

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoStrikes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of list strike price entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListStatusType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the status type. Valid values: 1 = Ack 2 = Response 3 = Timed 4 = ExecStarted 5 = AllDone 6 = Alert

FixFieldSpec.Name: NetGrossInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross. Valid values: 1 = Net 2 = Gross

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListOrderStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the status of a list order. Valid values: 1 = InBiddingProcess 2 = ReceivedForExecution 3 = Executing 4 = Canceling 5 = Alert 6 = All Done 7 = Reject

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExpireDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market’s business practices

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListExecInstType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of ListExecInst (69). Valid values: 1 = Immediate 2 = Wait for Execute Instruction (e.g. a List Execute message or phone call before proceeding with execution of the list) 3 = Exchange/switch CIV order – Sell driven 4 = Exchange/switch CIV order – Buy driven, cash top-up (i.e. additional cash will be provided to fulfil the order) 5 = Exchange/switch CIV order – Buy driven, cash withdraw (i.e. additional cash will not be provided to fulfil the order)

FixFieldSpec.Name: CxlRejResponseTo
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of request that a Cancel Reject is in response to. Valid values: 1 = Order Cancel Request 2 = Order Cancel/Replace Request

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingCouponRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraTradeQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity traded with the ContraBroker (375).

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraTradeTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker (375). (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as “GMT”)

FixFieldSpec.Name: LiquidityNumSecurities
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MultiLegReportingType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate what an Execution Report represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securities, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.). Valid Values: 1 = Single Security (default if not specified) 2 = Individual leg of a multi-leg security 3 = Multi-leg security

FixFieldSpec.Name: StrikeTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ListStatusText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format text string related to List Status.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText (446) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedListStatusText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText (444) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PartyIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies class or source of the PartyID (448) value. Required if PartyID is specified. Note: applicable values depend upon PartyRole (452) specified. See “Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block” Valid values: Applicable to all PartyRoles unless otherwise specified: B = BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) code (ISO 9362 - See "Appendix 6-B") C = Generally accepted market participant identifier (e.g. NASD mnemonic) D = Proprietary/Custom code E = ISO Country Code F = Settlement Entity Location (note if Local Market Settlement use “E = ISO Country Code”) (see “Appendix 6-G” for valid values) G = MIC (ISO 10383 - Market Identifier Code) (See "Appendix 6-C") H = CSD participant/member code (e.g. Euroclear, DTC, CREST or Kassenverein number) For PartyRole="Investor ID" and for Equities: 1 = Korean Investor ID 2 = Taiwanese Qualified Foreign Investor ID QFII / FID 3 = Taiwanese Trading Account 4 = Malaysian Central Depository (MCD) number 5 = Chinese B Share (Shezhen and Shanghai) See Volume 4: “Example Usage of PartyRole="Investor ID" ” For PartyRole="Investor ID" and for CIV: 6 = UK National Insurance or Pension Number 7 = US Social Security Number 8 = US Employer Identification Number 9 = Australian Business Number A = Australian Tax File Number For PartyRole="Broker of Credit": I = Directed broker three character acronym as defined in ISITC ‘ETC Best Practice’ guidelines document

FixFieldSpec.Name: PartyID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452). See “Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block”

FixFieldSpec.Name: NetChgPrevDay
FixFieldSpec.Description: Net change from previous day’s closing price vs. last traded price.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PartyRole
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID (448) specified. See “Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block” Valid values: 1 = Executing Firm (formerly FIX 4.2 ExecBroker) 2 = Broker of Credit (formerly FIX 4.2 BrokerOfCredit) 3 = Client ID (formerly FIX 4.2 ClientID) 4 = Clearing Firm (formerly FIX 4.2 ClearingFirm) 5 = Investor ID 6 = Introducing Firm 7 = Entering Firm 8 = Locate/Lending Firm (for short-sales) 9 = Fund manager Client ID (for CIV) 10 = Settlement Location (formerly FIX 4.2 SettlLocation) 11 = Order Origination Trader (associated with Order Origination Firm – e.g. trader who initiates/submits the order) 12 = Executing Trader (associated with Executing Firm - actually executes) 13 = Order Origination Firm (e.g. buyside firm) 14 = Giveup Clearing Firm (firm to which trade is given up) 15 = Correspondant Clearing Firm 16 = Executing System 17 = Contra Firm 18 = Contra Clearing Firm 19 = Sponsoring Firm 20 = Underlying Contra Firm (…values continued in next row….) 20 = Underlying Contra Firm 21 = Clearing Organization 22 = Exchange 24 = Customer Account 25 = Correspondent Clearing Organization 26 = Correspondent Broker 27 = Buyer/Seller (Receiver/Deliverer) 28 = Custodian 29 = Intermediary 30 = Agent 31 = Sub custodian 32 = Beneficiary 33 = Interested party 34 = Regulatory body 35 = Liquidity provider 36 = Entering Trader 37 = Contra Trader 38 = Position Account (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoPartyIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole (452) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoSecurityAltID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of SecurityAltID (455) entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityAltID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource (456) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityAltIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID (455) value. Required if SecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoUnderlyingSecurityAltID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

FixFieldSpec.Name: Product
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (461) and SecurityType (167) fields. Valid values: 1 = AGENCY 2 = COMMODITY 3 = CORPORATE 4 = CURRENCY 5 = EQUITY 6 = GOVERNMENT 7 = INDEX 8 = LOAN 9 = MONEYMARKET 10 = MORTGAGE 11 = MUNICIPAL 12 = OTHER 13 = FINANCING

FixFieldSpec.Name: CFICode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 10962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards". See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (167) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments. A subset of possible values applicable to FIX usage are identified in "Appendix 6-D CFICode Usage - ISO 10962 Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code)"

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingProduct
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s Product. Valid values: see Product(460) field

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingCFICode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s CFICode. Valid values: see CFICode (461)field

FixFieldSpec.Name: TestMessageIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a “test” vs. “production” connection. Useful for preventing “accidents”. Valid values: Y = True (Test) N = False (Production)

FixFieldSpec.Name: BookingRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

FixFieldSpec.Name: IndividualAllocID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs (78) repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount).

FixFieldSpec.Name: RoundingDirection
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies which direction to round For CIV – indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where CashOrdQty (152) or (for CIV only) OrderPercent (516) are specified on an order. Valid values are: 0 = Round to nearest 1 = Round down 2 = Round up The default is for rounding to be at the discretion of the executing broker or fund manager. e.g. for an order specifying CashOrdQty or OrderPercent if the calculated number of shares/units was 325.76 and RoundingModulus (469) was 10 – “round down” would give 320 units, “round up” would give 330 units and “round to nearest” would give 320 units.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RoundingModulus
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required. i.e. 10 means round to a multiple of 10 units/shares; 0.5 means round to a multiple of 0.5 units/shares. The default, if RoundingDirection (468) is specified without RoundingModulus, is to round to a whole unit/share.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CountryOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (48) (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

FixFieldSpec.Name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LocaleOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the locale. For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to http://www.atmos.albany.edu/cgi/stagrep-cgi Reference the IATA city codes for values. Note IATA (International Air Transport Association) maintains the codes at www.iata.org.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoRegistDtls
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions message

FixFieldSpec.Name: MailingDtls
FixFieldSpec.Description: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

FixFieldSpec.Name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
FixFieldSpec.Description: The ISO 3166 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PaymentRef
FixFieldSpec.Description: “Settlement Payment Reference” – A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DistribPaymentMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution. 1 = CREST 2 = NSCC 3 = Euroclear 4 = Clearstream 5 = Cheque 6 = Telegraphic Transfer 7 = FedWire 8 = Direct Credit (BECS, BACS) 9 = ACH Credit 10 = BPAY 11 = High Value Clearing System (HVACS) 12 = Reinvest in fund 13 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashDistribCurr
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies currency to be use for Cash Distributions– see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

FixFieldSpec.Name: CommCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies currency to be use for Commission (12) if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

FixFieldSpec.Name: CancellationRights
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV – A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies. Valid values are: Y = Yes N = No – execution only M = No – waiver agreement O = No – institutional.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: A one character code identifying Money laundering status. Valid values: Y = Passed N = Not checked 1 = Exempt – Below The Limit 2 = Exempt – Client Money Type Exemption 3 = Exempt – Authorised Credit or Financial Institution.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MailingInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

FixFieldSpec.Name: TransBkdTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx (31) was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point. Valid values are: B = Bid price C = Creation price D = Creation price plus adjustment % E = Creation price plus adjustment amount O = Offer price P = Offer price minus adjustment % Q = Offer price minus adjustment amount S = Single price

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecPriceAdjustment
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType (484)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DateOfBirth
FixFieldSpec.Description: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeReportTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies Trade Report message transaction type Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Cancel 2 = Replace 3 = Release 4 = Reverse (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type char)

FixFieldSpec.Name: CardHolderName
FixFieldSpec.Description: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CardNumber
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CardExpDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CardIssNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PaymentMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: A code identifying the Settlement payment method. 1 = CREST 2 = NSCC 3 = Euroclear 4 = Clearstream 5 = Cheque 6 = Telegraphic Transfer 7 = FedWire 8 = Debit Card 9 = Direct Debit (BECS) 10 = Direct Credit (BECS) 11 = Credit Card 12 = ACH Debit 13 = ACH Credit 14 = BPAY 15 = High Value Clearing System (HVACS) 16 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistAcctType
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV – a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund manager’s account types is required.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Designation
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a broker’s nominee or street name.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TaxAdvantageType
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held. 0=None/Not Applicable (default) 1 = Maxi ISA (UK) 2 = TESSA (UK) 3 = Mini Cash ISA (UK) 4 = Mini Stocks and Shares ISA (UK) 5 = Mini Insurance ISA (UK) 6 = Current year payment (US) 7 = Prior year payment (US) 8 = Asset transfer (US) 9 = Employee - prior year (US) 10 = Employee – current year (US) 11 = Employer - prior year (US) 12 = Employer – current year (US) 13 = Non-fund prototype IRA (US) 14 = Non-fund qualified plan (US) 15 = Defined contribution plan (US) 16 = Individual Retirement Account (US) 17 = Individual Retirement Account – Rollover (US) 18 = KEOGH (US) 19 = Profit Sharing Plan (US) 20 = 401K (US) 21 = Self-Directed IRA (US) 22 = 403(b) (US) 23 = 457 (US) 24 = Roth IRA (fund prototype) (US) 25 = Roth IRA (non-prototype) (US) 26 = Roth Conversion IRA (fund prototype) (US) 27 = Roth Conversion IRA (non-prototype) (US) 28 = Education IRA (fund prototype) (US) 29 = Education IRA (non-prototype) (US) 30 – 998 are reserved for future use by recognized taxation authorities 999=Other values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistRejReasonText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instruction has been rejected.

FixFieldSpec.Name: FundRenewWaiv
FixFieldSpec.Description: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived. Valid values are: Y = Yes N = No

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashDistribAgentName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashDistribAgentCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
FixFieldSpec.Description: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashDistribPayRef
FixFieldSpec.Description: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctName
FixFieldSpec.Description: Name of account at agent bank for distributions.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CardStartDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PaymentDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PaymentRemitterID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager: A = Accepted R = Rejected H = Held N = Reminder – i.e. Registration Instructions are still outstanding

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistRejReasonCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions has been rejected.Possible values of reason code include: 1 = Invalid/unacceptable Account Type2 = Invalid/unacceptable Tax Exempt Type3 = Invalid/unacceptable Ownership Type4 = Invalid/unacceptable No Reg Detls5 = Invalid/unacceptable Reg Seq No6 = Invalid/unacceptable Reg Dtls7 = Invalid/unacceptable Mailing Dtls8 = Invalid/unacceptable Mailing Inst9 = Invalid/unacceptable Investor ID10 = Invalid/unacceptable Investor ID Source11 = Invalid/unacceptable Date of Birth12 = Invalid/unacceptable Investor Country Of Residence13 = Invalid/unacceptable NoDistribInstns14 = Invalid/unacceptable Distrib Percentage15 = Invalid/unacceptable Distrib Payment Method 16 = Invalid/unacceptable Cash Distrib Agent Acct Name17 = Invalid/unacceptable Cash Distrib Agent Code18 = Invalid/unacceptable Cash Distrib Agent Acct Num 99 = Other The reason may be further amplified in the RegistRejReasonCode field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier for the RegistID (513) with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType (514) transaction types.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistDtls
FixFieldSpec.Description: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoDistribInsts
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions message

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistEmail
FixFieldSpec.Description: Email address relating to Registration name and address details

FixFieldSpec.Name: DistribPercentage
FixFieldSpec.Description: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RegistTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies Registration Instructions transaction type Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Replace 2 = Cancel

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExecValuationPoint
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderPercent
FixFieldSpec.Description: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investor’s total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investor’s cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty (38) in shares/units for subsequent messages.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OwnershipType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The relationship between Registration parties. J = Joint Investors T = Tenants in Common 2 = Joint Trustees

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoContAmts
FixFieldSpec.Description: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report message

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContAmtType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of ContAmtValue (520). For UK valid values include: 1 = Commission Amount (actual) 2 = Commission % (actual) 3 = Initial Charge Amount 4 = Initial Charge % 5 = Discount Amount 6 = Discount % 7 = Dilution Levy Amount 8 = Dilution Levy % 9 = Exit Charge Amount 10 = Exit Charge % 11 = Fund-based Renewal Commission % (a.k.a. Trail commission) 12 = Projected Fund Value (i.e. for investments intended to realise or exceed a specific future value) 13 = Fund-based Renewal Commission Amount (based on Order value) 14 = Fund-based Renewal Commission Amount (based on Projected Fund value) 15 = Net Settlement Amount NOTE That Commission Amount / % in Contract Amounts is the commission actually charged, rather than the commission instructions given in Fields 12/13.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContAmtValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType (519).

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContAmtCurr
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

FixFieldSpec.Name: OwnerType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of owner. Valid values: 1 = Individual Investor 2 = Public Company 3 = Private Company 4 = Individual Trustee 5 = Company Trustee 6 = Pension Plan 7 = Custodian Under Gifts to Minors Act 8 = Trusts 9 = Fiduciaries 10 = Networking Sub-Account 11 = Non-Profit Organization 12 = Corporate Body 13 =Nominee

FixFieldSpec.Name: PartySubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole (452)=Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole=Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NestedPartyID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NestedPartyIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyIDSource value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecondaryClOrdID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID (11) used by an exchange or executing system.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecondaryExecID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID (17) used by an exchange or executing system.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderCapacity
FixFieldSpec.Description: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order. Valid values: A = Agency G = Proprietary I = Individual P = Principal (Note for CMS purposes, Principal includes Proprietary) R = Riskless Principal W = Agent for Other Member (as of FIX 4.3, this field replaced Rule80A (tag 47) --used in conjunction with OrderRestrictions (529) field) (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderRestrictions
FixFieldSpec.Description: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space. Valid values: 1 = Program Trade 2 = Index Arbitrage 3 = Non-Index Arbitrage 4 = Competing Market Maker 5 = Acting as Market Maker or Specialist in the security 6 = Acting as Market Maker or Specialist in the underlying security of a derivative security 7 = Foreign Entity (of foreign governmnet or regulatory jurisdiction) 8 = External Market Participant 9 = External Inter-connected Market Linkage A = Riskless Arbitrage

FixFieldSpec.Name: MassCancelRequestType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request. Valid values: 1 = Cancel orders for a security 2 = Cancel orders for an Underlying security 3 = Cancel orders for a Product 4 = Cancel orders for a CFICode 5 = Cancel orders for a SecurityType 6 = Cancel orders for a trading session 7 = Cancel all orders

FixFieldSpec.Name: MassCancelResponse
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request Valid values: 0 = Cancel Request Rejected -- See MassCancelRejectReason (532) 1 = Cancel orders for a security 2 = Cancel orders for an Underlying security 3 = Cancel orders for a Product 4 = Cancel orders for a CFICode 5 = Cancel orders for a SecurityType 6 = Cancel orders for a trading session 7 = Cancel all orders

FixFieldSpec.Name: MassCancelRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request was rejected Valid valuess: 0 = Mass Cancel Not Supported 1 = Invalid or unknown Security 2 = Invalid or unknown underlying 3 = Invalid or unknown Product 4 = Invalid or unknown CFICode 5 = Invalid or unknown Security Type 6 = Invalid or unknown trading session 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotalAffectedOrders
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of orders affected by mass cancel request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoAffectedOrders
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AffectedOrderID
FixFieldSpec.Description: OrderID (37) of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
FixFieldSpec.Description: SecondaryOrderID (198) of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of quote. Valid values: 0 = Indicative 1 = Tradeable 2 = Restricted Tradeable 3 = Counter (tradable) An indicative quote is used to inform a counterparty of a market. An indicative quote does not result directly in a trade. A tradeable quote is submitted to a market and will result directly in a trade against other orders and quotes in a market. A restricted tradeable quote is submitted to a market and within a certain restriction (possibly based upon price or quantity) will automatically trade against orders. Order that do not comply with restrictions are sent to the quote issuer who can choose to accept or decline the order. A counter quote is used in the negotiation model. See Volume 7 – Product: Fixed Income for example usage.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NestedPartyRole
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyRole value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoNestedPartyIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of NestedPartyID (524), NestedPartyIDSource (525), and NestedPartyRole (538) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaturityDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Date of maturity.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingMaturityDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s maturity date. See MaturityDate (541) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: InstrRegistry
FixFieldSpec.Description: The location at which records of ownership are maintained for this instrument, and at which ownership changes must be recorded. Valid values: BIC (Bank Identification Code—Swift managed) = the depository or custodian who maintains ownership Records ISO Country Code = country in which registry is kept "ZZ" = physical or bearer

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashMargin
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies whether an order is a margin order or a non-margin order. This is primarily used when sending orders to Japanese exchanges to indicate sell margin or buy to cover. The same tag could be assigned also by buy-side to indicate the intent to sell or buy margin and the sell-side to accept or reject (base on some validation criteria) the margin request. Valid values: 1 = Cash 2 = Margin Open 3 = Margin Close

FixFieldSpec.Name: NestedPartySubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartySubID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Scope
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the scope of a data element. Valid values: 1 = Local (Exchange, ECN, ATS) 2 = National 3 = Global

FixFieldSpec.Name: MDImplicitDelete
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines how a server handles distribution of a truncated book. Defaults to broker option. Valid values: Y = Client has responsibility for implicitly deleting bids or offers falling outside the MarketDepth of the request. N = Server must send an explicit delete for bids or offers falling outside the requested MarketDepth of the request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CrossID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifier for a cross order. Must be unique during a given trading day. Recommend that firms use the order date as part of the CrossID for Good Till Cancel (GT) orders.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CrossType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of cross being submitted to a market Valid values: 1 = Cross Trade which is executed completely or not. Both sides are treated in the same manner. This is equivalent to an All or None. 2 = Cross Trade which is executed partially and the rest is cancelled. One side is fully executed, the other side is partially executed with the remainder being cancelled. This is equivalent to an Immediate or Cancel on the other side. Note: The CrossPrioritzation (550) field may be used to indicate which side should fully execute in this scenario. 3 = Cross trade which is partially executed with the unfilled portions remaining active. One side of the cross is fully executed (as denoted with the CrossPrioritization field), but the unfilled portion remains active. 4 = Cross trade is executed with existing orders with the same price. In the case other orders exist with the same price, the quantity of the Cross is executed against the existing orders and quotes, the remainder of the cross is executed against the other side of the cross. The two sides potentially have different quantities.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CrossPrioritization
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates if one side or the other of a cross order should be prioritized. 0 = None 1 = Buy side is prioritized 2 = Sell side is prioritized The definition of prioritization is left to the market. In some markets prioritization means which side of the cross order is applied to the market first. In other markets – prioritization may mean that the prioritized side is fully executed (sometimes referred to as the side being protected).

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigCrossID
FixFieldSpec.Description: CrossID of the previous cross order (NOT the initial cross order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous cross order in Cross Cancel and Cross Cancel/Replace Requests.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoSides
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Side repeating group instances. Valid values: 1 = one side 2 = both sides

FixFieldSpec.Name: Username
FixFieldSpec.Description: Userid or username.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Password
FixFieldSpec.Description: Password or passphrase.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoLegs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of InstrumentLeg repeating group instances.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency associated with a particular Leg's quantity

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoSecurityTypes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates total number of security types in the event that multiple Security Type messages are used to return results (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named TotalNumSecurityTypes)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoSecurityTypes
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Security Type repeating group instances.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityListRequestType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type/criteria of Security List Request Valid values: 0 = Symbol 1 = SecurityType and/or CFICode 2 = Product 3 = TradingSessionID 4 = All Securities

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecurityRequestResult
FixFieldSpec.Description: The results returned to a Security Request message Valid values: 0 = Valid request 1 = Invalid or unsupported request 2 = No instruments found that match selection criteria 3 = Not authorized to retrieve instrument data 4 = Instrument data temporarily unavailable 5 = Request for instrument data not supported

FixFieldSpec.Name: RoundLot
FixFieldSpec.Description: The trading lot size of a security

FixFieldSpec.Name: MinTradeVol
FixFieldSpec.Description: The minimum trading volume for a security

FixFieldSpec.Name: MultiLegRptTypeReq
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the method of execution reporting requested by issuer of the order. 0 = Report by mulitleg security only (Do not report legs) 1 = Report by multileg security and by instrument legs belonging to the multileg security. 2 = Report by instrument legs belonging to the multileg security only (Do not report status of multileg security)

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegPositionEffect
FixFieldSpec.Description: PositionEffect for leg of a multileg See PositionEffect (77) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegCoveredOrUncovered
FixFieldSpec.Description: CoveredOrUncovered for leg of a multileg See CoveredOrUncovered (203) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price for leg of a multileg See Price (44) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradSesStatusRejReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the reason a Trading Session Status Request was rejected. Valid values: 1 = Unknown or invalid TradingSessionID 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeRequestID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Trade Capture Report Request ID

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeRequestType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Trade Capture Report. Valid values: 0 = All trades 1 = Matched trades matching Criteria provided on request (parties, exec id, trade id, order id, instrument, input source, etc.) 2 = Unmatched trades that match criteria 3 = Unreported trades that match criteria 4 = Advisories that match criteria

FixFieldSpec.Name: PreviouslyReported
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates if the trade capture report was previously reported to the counterparty Valid values: Y = previously reported to counterparty N = not reported to counterparty

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeReportID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier of trade capture report

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeReportRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MatchStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: The status of this trade with respect to matching or comparison. Valid values: 0 = compared, matched or affirmed 1 = uncompared, unmatched, or unaffirmed 2 = advisory or alert

FixFieldSpec.Name: MatchType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The point in the matching process at which this trade was matched. Valid values: For NYSE and AMEX: A1 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus four badges and execution time (within two-minute window) A2 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus four badges A3 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus two badges and execution time (within two-minute window) A4 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus two badges A5 = Exact match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator plus execution time (within two-minute window) AQ = Compared records resulting from stamped advisories or specialist accepts/pair-offs S1 to S5 = Summarized Match using A1 to A5 exact match criteria except quantity is summarized M1 = Exact Match on Trade Date, Stock Symbol, Quantity, Price, Trade Type, and Special Trade Indicator minus badges and times M2 = Summarized Match minus badges and times MT = OCS Locked In (…values continued in next row….) For NASDAQ: M1 = ACT M1 Match M2 = ACT M2 Match M3 = ACT Accepted Trade M4 = ACT Default Trade M5 = ACT Default After M2 M6 = ACT M6 Match MT = Non-ACT

FixFieldSpec.Name: OddLot
FixFieldSpec.Description: This trade is to be treated as an odd lot Values: Y = treat as odd lot N = treat as round lot If this field is not specified, the default will be "N"

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoClearingInstructions
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of clearing instructions

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClearingInstruction
FixFieldSpec.Description: Eligibility of this trade for clearing and central counterparty processing Valid values: 0 = process normally 1 = exclude from all netting 2 = bilateral netting only 3 = ex clearing 4 = special trade 5 = multilateral netting 6 = clear against central counterparty 7 = exclude from central counterparty 8 = Manual mode (pre-posting and/or pre-giveup) 9 = Automatic posting mode (trade posting to the position account number specified) 10 = Automatic give-up mode (trade give-up to the give-up destination number specified) 11 = Qualified Service Representative (QSR) - 12 = Customer Trade 13 = Self clearing values above 4000 are reserved for agreement between parties

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeInputSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of input device or system from which the trade was entered.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeInputDevice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specific device number, terminal number or station where trade was entered

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoDates
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Date fields provided in date range

FixFieldSpec.Name: AccountType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of account associated with an order Valid values: 1 = Account is carried on customer Side of Books 2 = Account is carried on non-Customer Side of books 3 = House Trader 4 = Floor Trader 6 = Account is carried on non-customer side of books and is cross margined 7 = Account is house trader and is cross margined 8 = Joint Backoffice Account (JBO)

FixFieldSpec.Name: CustOrderCapacity
FixFieldSpec.Description: Capacity of customer placing the order 1 = Member trading for their own account 2 = Clearing Firm trading for its proprietary account 3 = Member trading for another member 4 = All other Primarily used by futures exchanges to indicate the CTICode (customer type indicator) as required by the US CFTC (Commodity Futures Trading Commission).

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClOrdLinkID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Permits order originators to tie together groups of orders in which trades resulting from orders are associated for a specific purpose, for example the calculation of average execution price for a customer or to associate lists submitted to a broker as waves of a larger program trade.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MassStatusReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Value assigned by issuer of Mass Status Request to uniquely identify the request

FixFieldSpec.Name: MassStatusReqType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Mass Status Request Type Valid values: 1 = Status for orders for a security 2 = Status for orders for an Underlying security 3 = Status for orders for a Product 4 = Status for orders for a CFICode 5 = Status for orders for a SecurityType 6 = Status for orders for a trading session 7 = Status for all orders 8 = Status for orders for a PartyID

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigOrdModTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: The most recent (or current) modification TransactTime (tag 60) reported on an Execution Report for the order. The OrigOrdModTime is provided as an optional field on Order Cancel Request and Order Cancel Replace Requests to identify that the state of the order has not changed since the request was issued. This is provided to support markets similar to Eurex and A/C/E.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSettlType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Refer to values for SettlType[63] (formerly named LegSettlmntTyp prior to FIX 4.4)

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSettlDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Refer to description for SettlDate[64] (formerly named LegFutSettlDate prior to FIX 4.4)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DayBookingInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not automatic booking can occur. 0 = Can trigger booking without reference to the order initiator ("auto") 1 = Speak with order initiator before booking ("speak first") 2 = Accumulate

FixFieldSpec.Name: BookingUnit
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates what constitutes a bookable unit. 0 = Each partial execution is a bookable unit 1 = Aggregate partial executions on this order, and book one trade per order 2 = Aggregate executions for this symbol, side, and settlement date

FixFieldSpec.Name: PreallocMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the method of preallocation. 0 = Pro-rata 1 = Do not pro-rata = discuss first

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingCountryOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingStateOrProvinceOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingLocaleOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingInstrRegistry
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s InstrRegistry. See InstrRegistry (543) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegCountryOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security’s CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegStateOrProvinceOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security’s StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegLocaleOfIssue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security’s LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegInstrRegistry
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual leg security’s InstrRegistry. See InstrRegistry (543) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSymbol
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s Symbol. See Symbol (55) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSymbolSfx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SymbolSfx. See SymbolSfx (65) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSecurityID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityID. See SecurityID (48) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSecurityIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityIDSource. See SecurityIDSource (22) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoLegSecurityAltID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s NoSecurityAltID. See NoSecurityAltID (454) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSecurityAltID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityAltID. See SecurityAltID (455) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSecurityAltIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityAltIDSource. See SecurityAltIDSource (456) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegProduct
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s Product. See Product (460) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegCFICode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s CFICode. See CFICode (461) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSecurityType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityType. See SecurityType (167) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegMaturityMonthYear
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s MaturityMonthYear. See MaturityMonthYear (200) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegMaturityDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s MaturityDate. See MaturityDate (541) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegStrikePrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s StrikePrice. See StrikePrice (202) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegOptAttribute
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s OptAttribute. See OptAttribute (206) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegContractMultiplier
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegCouponRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSecurityExchange
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityExchange. See SecurityExchange (207) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegIssuer
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s Issuer. See Issuer (106) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedLegIssuerLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s EncodedIssuerLen. See EncodedIssuerLen (348) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedLegIssuer
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s EncodedIssuer. See EncodedIssuer (349) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityDesc. See SecurityDesc (107) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedLegSecurityDescLen
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s EncodedSecurityDescLen. See EncodedSecurityDescLen (350) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: EncodedLegSecurityDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s EncodedSecurityDesc. See EncodedSecurityDesc (351) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegRatioQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: The ratio of quantity for this individual leg relative to the entire multileg security.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSide
FixFieldSpec.Description: The side of this individual leg (multileg security). See Side (54) field for description and values

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradingSessionSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Optional market assigned sub identifier for a trading session. Usage is determined by market or counterparties. Used by US based futures markets to identify exchange specific execution time bracket codes as required by US market regulations.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Describes the specific type or purpose of an Allocation message (i.e. "Buyside Calculated") Valid values: 1 = Calculated (includes MiscFees and NetMoney) 2 = Preliminary (without MiscFees and NetMoney) 3 = Sellside Calculated Using Preliminary (includes MiscFees and NetMoney) (Replaced) 4 = Sellside Calculated Without Preliminary (sent unsolicited by sellside, includes MiscFees and NetMoney) (Replaced) 5 = Ready-To-Book - Single Order 6 = Buyside Ready-To-Book - Combined Set of Orders (Replaced) 7 = Warehouse instruction 8 = Request to Intermediary (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions) *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoHops
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of HopCompID entries in repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: HopCompID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify the third party firm which delivered a specific message either from the firm which originated the message or from another third party (if multiple “hops” are performed). It is recommended that this value be the SenderCompID (49) of the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or “hubs”. Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

FixFieldSpec.Name: HopSendingTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Time that HopCompID (628) sent the message. It is recommended that this value be the SendingTime (52) of the message sent by the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or “hubs”. Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

FixFieldSpec.Name: HopRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier assigned by HopCompID (628) associated with the message sent. It is recommended that this value be the MsgSeqNum (34) of the message sent by the third party. Applicable when messages are communicated/re-distributed via third parties which function as service bureaus or “hubs”. Only applicable if OnBehalfOfCompID (115) is being used.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MidPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Mid price/rate

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidYield
FixFieldSpec.Description: Bid yield

FixFieldSpec.Name: MidYield
FixFieldSpec.Description: Mid yield

FixFieldSpec.Name: OfferYield
FixFieldSpec.Description: Offer yield

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClearingFeeIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates type of fee being assessed of the customer for trade executions at an exchange. Applicable for futures markets only at this time. Valid Values (source CBOT, CME, NYBOT, and NYMEX): B = CBOE Member C = Non-member and Customer E = Equity Member and Clearing Member F = Full and Associate Member trading for own account and as floor Brokers H = 106.H and 106.J Firms I = GIM, IDEM and COM Membership Interest Holders L = Lessee and 106.F Employees M = All other ownership types 1 = 1st year delegate trading for his own account 2 = 2nd year delegate trading for his own account 3 = 3rd year delegate trading for his own account 4 = 4th year delegate trading for his own account 5 = 5th year delegate trading for his own account 9 = 6th year and beyond delegate trading for his own account

FixFieldSpec.Name: WorkingIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates if the order is currently being worked. Applicable only for OrdStatus = “New”. For open outcry markets this indicates that the order is being worked in the crowd. For electronic markets it indicates that the order has transitioned from a contingent order to a market order. Valid values: Y = Order is currently being worked N = Order has been accepted but not yet in a working state

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegLastPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Execution price assigned to a leg of a multileg instrument. See LastPx (31) field for description and values

FixFieldSpec.Name: PriorityIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates if a Cancel/Replace has caused an order to lose book priority. Valid values: 0 = Priority Unchanged 1 = Lost Priority as result of order change

FixFieldSpec.Name: PriceImprovement
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amount of price improvement.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Price2
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price of the future part of a F/X swap order. See Price (44) for description.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastForwardPoints2
FixFieldSpec.Description: F/X forward points of the future part of a F/X swap order added to LastSpotRate (194). May be a negative value.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BidForwardPoints2
FixFieldSpec.Description: Bid F/X forward points of the future portion of a F/X swap quote added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OfferForwardPoints2
FixFieldSpec.Description: Offer F/X forward points of the future portion of a F/X swap quote added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RFQReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: RFQ Request ID – used to identify an RFQ Request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MktBidPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate the best bid in a market

FixFieldSpec.Name: MktOfferPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate the best offer in a market

FixFieldSpec.Name: MinBidSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate a minimum quantity for a bid. If this field is used the BidSize (134) field is interpreted as the maximum bid size

FixFieldSpec.Name: MinOfferSize
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate a minimum quantity for an offer. If this field is used the OfferSize (135) field is interpreted as the maximum offer size.

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteStatusReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for Quote Status Request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegalConfirm
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates that this message is to serve as the final and legal confirmation. Valid values: Y = Legal confirm N = Does not constitute a legal confirm

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingLastPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: The calculated or traded price for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingLastQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: The calculated or traded quantity for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique indicator for a specific leg.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraLegRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique indicator for a specific leg for the ContraBroker (375).

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlCurrBidFxRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the bid “SettlCurrAmt” (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlCurrOfferFxRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the offer “SettlCurrAmt” (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteRequestRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason Quote was rejected: Valid Values: 1 = Unknown symbol (Security) 2 = Exchange(Security) closed 3 = Quote Request exceeds limit 4 = Too late to enter 5 = Invalid price 6 = Not authorized to request quote 7 = No match for inquiry 8 = No market for instrument 9 = No inventory 10 = Pass 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideComplianceID
FixFieldSpec.Description: ID within repeating group of sides which is used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

FixFieldSpec.Name: AcctIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to identify the source of the Account (1) code. This is especially useful if the account is a new account that the Respondent may not have setup yet in their system. Valid values: 1 = BIC 2 = SID code 3 = TFM (GSPTA) 4 = OMGEO (AlertID) 5 = DTCC code 99 = Other (custom or proprietary)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocAcctIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to identify the source of the AllocAccount (79) code. See AcctIDSource (660) for valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BenchmarkPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies the price of the benchmark.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BenchmarkPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies type of BenchmarkPrice (662). See PriceType (423) for valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ConfirmID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Message reference for Confirmation

FixFieldSpec.Name: ConfirmStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the status of the Confirmation. Valid values: 1 = Received 2 = Mismatched account 3 = Missing settlement instructions 4 = Confirmed 5 = Request rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: ConfirmTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the Confirmation transaction type. Valid values: 0 = New 1 = Replace 2 = Cancel

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContractSettlMonth
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DeliveryForm
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the form of delivery. Valid values: 1 = BookEntry [the default] 2 = Bearer

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastParPx

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegBenchmarkCurveCurrency

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegBenchmarkCurveName
