FixFieldSpec.Name: LegBenchmarkCurvePoint
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the point on the Leg Benchmark Curve. See BenchmarkCurvePoint (222) for description and valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegBenchmarkPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to identify the price of the benchmark security. See BenchmarkPrice (662) for description and valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegBenchmarkPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The price type of the LegBenchmarkPrice. See BenchmarkPriceType (663) for description and valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegBidPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Bid price of this leg. See BidPx (132) for description and valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegIOIQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Leg-specific IOI quantity. See IOIQty (27) for description and valid values

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoLegStipulations
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of leg stipulation entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegOfferPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Offer price of this leg. See OfferPx (133) for description and valid values

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegOrderQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity ordered of this leg. See OrderQty (38) for description and valid values

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The price type of the LegBidPx (681) and/or LegOfferPx (684). See PriceType (423) for description and valid values

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity of this leg, e.g. in Quote dialog. See Quantity (53) for description and valid values

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegStipulationType
FixFieldSpec.Description: For Fixed Income, type of Stipulation for this leg. See StipulationType (233) for description and valid values

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegStipulationValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: For Fixed Income, value of stipulation. See StipulationValue (234) for description and valid values

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSwapType
FixFieldSpec.Description: For Fixed Income, used instead of LegQty (687) or LegOrderQty (685) to requests the respondent to calculate the quantity based on the quantity on the opposite side of the swap. Valid values: 1 = Par For Par 2 = Modified Duration 4 = Risk 5 = Proceeds

FixFieldSpec.Name: Pool
FixFieldSpec.Description: For Fixed Income, identifies MBS / ABS pool.

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuotePriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent price type requested in Quote. Valid values: 1 = percent (percent of par) 2 = per share (e.g. cents per share) 3 = fixed amount (absolute value) 4 = discount – percentage points below par 5 = premium – percentage points over par 6 = basis points relative to benchmark 7 = TED price 8 = TED yield 9 = Yield spread (swaps) 10 = Yield If the Quote Request is for a Swap values 1-8 apply to all legs.

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteRespID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Message reference for Quote Response

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteRespType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of Quote Response. Valid values: 1 = Hit/Lift 2 = Counter 3 = Expired 4 = Cover 5 = Done Away 6 = Pass

FixFieldSpec.Name: QuoteQualifier
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to qualify Quote use See IOIQualifier (104) for description and valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: YieldRedemptionDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Date to which the yield has been calculated (i.e. maturity, par call or current call, pre-refunded date).

FixFieldSpec.Name: YieldRedemptionPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price to which the yield has been calculated.

FixFieldSpec.Name: YieldRedemptionPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The price type of the YieldRedemptionPrice (697) See PriceType (423) for description and valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: BenchmarkSecurityID
FixFieldSpec.Description: The identifier of the benchmark security, e.g. Treasury against Corporate bond. See SecurityID (tag 48) for description and valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ReversalIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates a trade that reverses a previous trade.

FixFieldSpec.Name: YieldCalcDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Include as needed to clarify yield irregularities associated with date, e.g. when it falls on a non-business day.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoPositions
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of position entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to identify the type of quantity that is being returned. Valid values: TQ = Transaction Quantity IAS = Intra-Spread Qty IES = Inter-Spread Qty FIN = End-of-Day Qty SOD = Start-of-Day Qty EX = Option Exercise Qty AS = Option Assignment TX = Transaction from Exercise TA = Transaction from Assignment PIT = Pit Trade Qty TRF = Transfer Trade Qty ETR = Electronic Trade Qty ALC = Allocation Trade Qty PA = Adjustment Qty ASF = As-of Trade Qty DLV = Delivery Qty TOT = Total Transaction Qty XM = Cross Margin Qty SPL = Integral Split

FixFieldSpec.Name: LongQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Long Quantity

FixFieldSpec.Name: ShortQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Short Quantity

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosQtyStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Status of this position. Valid values: 0 = Submitted 1 = Accepted 2 = Rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosAmtType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Position amount Valid values: FMTM = Final Mark-to-Market Amount IMTM = Incremental Mark-to-Market Amount TVAR = Trade Variation Amount SMTM = Start-of-Day Mark-to-Market Amount PREM = Premium Amount CRES = Cash Residual Amount CASH = Cash Amount (Corporate Event) VADJ = Value Adjusted Amount

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Position amount

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of position transaction Valid values: 1 = Exercise 2 = Do Not Exercise 3 = Position Adjustment 4 = Position Change Submission/Margin Disposition 5 = Pledge

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for the position maintenance request as assigned by the submitter

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoUnderlyings
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of underlying legs that make up the security.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosMaintAction
FixFieldSpec.Description: Maintenance Action to be performed. Valid values: 1 = New: used to increment the overall transaction quantity 2 = Replace: used to override the overall transaction quantity or specific add messages based on the reference id 3 = Cancel: used to remove the overall transaction or specific add messages based on reference id

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrigPosReqRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference to the PosReqID (710) of a previous maintenance request that is being replaced or canceled.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosMaintRptRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference to a PosMaintRptID (721) from a previous Position Maintenance Report that is being replaced or canceled.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ClearingBusinessDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: The "Clearing Business Date" referred to by this maintenance request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlSessID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies a specific settlement session Examples: ITD = Intraday RTH = Regular Trading Hours ETH = Electronic Trading Hours

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlSessSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: SubID value associated with SettlSessID (716)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AdjustmentType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of adjustment to be applied, used for PCS & PAJ Valid values: 0 = Process request as Margin Disposition 1 = Delta_plus 2 = Delta_minus 3 = Final

FixFieldSpec.Name: ContraryInstructionIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Required to be set to true (Y) when a position maintenance request is being performed contrary to current money position. Required when an exercise of an out of the money position is requested or an abandonement (do not exercise ) for an in the money position.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PriorSpreadIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates if requesting a rollover of prior day’s spread submissions.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosMaintRptID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for this position report

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosMaintStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Status of Position Maintenance Request Valid values: 0 = Accepted 1 = Accepted with Warnings 2 = Rejected 3 = Completed 4 = Completed with Warnings

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosMaintResult
FixFieldSpec.Description: Result of Position Maintenance Request. Valid values: 0 = Successful completion - no warnings or errors 1 = Rejected 99 = Other 4000+ Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user-defined values

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosReqType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for the position maintenance request as assigned by the submitter Valid values: 0 = Positions 1 = Trades 2 = Exercises 3 = Assignments

FixFieldSpec.Name: ResponseTransportType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies how the response to the request should be transmitted. Valid values: 0 = Inband: transport the request was sent over (Default) 1 = Out-of-Band: pre-arranged out of band delivery mechanism (i.e. FTP, HTTP, NDM, etc) between counterparties. Details specified via ResponseDestination (726).

FixFieldSpec.Name: ResponseDestination
FixFieldSpec.Description: URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) for details) or other pre-arranged value. Used in conjunction with ResponseTransportType (725) value of Out-of-Band to identify the out-of-band destination. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards"

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotalNumPosReports
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of Position Reports being returned.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosReqResult
FixFieldSpec.Description: Result of Request for Position Valid values: 0 = Valid Request 1 = Invalid or unsupported Request 2 = No positions found that match criteria 3 = Not authorized to request positions 4 = Request for Position not supported 99=Other (use Text(58) in conjunction with this code for an explanation) 4000+ Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user-defined values

FixFieldSpec.Name: PosReqStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Status of Request for Positions Valid values: 0 = Completed 1 = Completed with Warnings 2 = Rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Settlement price

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of settlement price Valid values: 1 = Final 2 = Theoretical

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSettlPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s SettlPrice. See SettlPrice (730) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSettlPriceType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s SettlPriceType. See SettlPriceType (731) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: PriorSettlPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Previous settlement price

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoQuoteQualifiers
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of repeating groups of QuoteQualifiers (695).

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocSettlCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency code of settlement denomination for a specific AllocAccount (79).

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocSettlCurrAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction) for a specific AllocAccount (79).

FixFieldSpec.Name: InterestAtMaturity
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amount of interest (i.e. lump-sum) at maturity.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegDatedDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: The effective date of a new securities issue determined by its underwriters. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Interest Accrual Date

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegPool
FixFieldSpec.Description: For Fixed Income, identifies MBS / ABS pool for a specific leg of a multi-leg instrument. See Pool (691) for description and valid values.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocInterestAtMaturity
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amount of interest (i.e. lump-sum) at maturity at the account-level.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocAccruedInterestAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income at the allocation-level.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DeliveryDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Date of delivery.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AssignmentMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Method under which assignment was conducted Valid values: R = Random P = ProRata

FixFieldSpec.Name: AssignmentUnit
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity Increment used in performing assignment.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OpenInterest
FixFieldSpec.Description: Open interest that was eligible for assignment.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExerciseMethod
FixFieldSpec.Description: Exercise Method used to in performing assignment. Valid values: A = Automatic M = Manual

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNumTradeReports
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of trade reports returned.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeRequestResult
FixFieldSpec.Description: Result of Trade Request Valid values: 0 = Successful (Default) 1 = Invalid or unknown instrument 2 = Invalid type of trade requested 3 = Invalid parties 4 = Invalid Transport Type requested 5 = Invalid Destination requested 8 = TradeRequestType not supported 9 = Unauthorized for Trade Capture Report Request 99 = Other 4000+ Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user-defined values

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeRequestStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Status of Trade Request. Valid values: 0 = Accepted 1 = Completed 2 = Rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeReportRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason Trade Capture Request was rejected. Valid values: 0 = Successful (Default) 1 = Invalid party information 2 = Unknown instrument 3 = Unauthorized to report trades 4 = Invalid trade type 99 = Other 4000+ Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user-defined values

FixFieldSpec.Name: SideMultiLegReportingType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate if the side being reported on Trade Capture Report represents a leg of a multileg instrument or a single security. Valid Values: 1 = Single Security (default if not specified) 2 = Individual leg of a multi-leg security 3 = Multi-leg security

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoPosAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of position amount entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AutoAcceptIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies whether or not an allocation has been automatically accepted on behalf of the Carry Firm by the Clearing House.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocReportID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for Allocation Report message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoNested2PartyIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Nested2PartyID (757), Nested2PartyIDSource (758), and Nested2PartyRole (759) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested2PartyID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyID value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested2PartyIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyIDSource value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested2PartyRole
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyRole value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested2PartySubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartySubID value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

FixFieldSpec.Name: BenchmarkSecurityIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies class or source of the BenchmarkSecurityID (699) value. Required if BenchmarkSecurityID is specified. Same values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecuritySubType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Sub-type qualification/identification of the SecurityType (e.g. for SecurityType="REPO"). Example Values: General = General Collateral (for SecurityType=REPO) For SecurityType="MLEG" markets can provide the name of the option or futures strategy, such as Calendar, Vertical, Butterfly, etc. NOTE: Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingSecuritySubType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying security’s SecuritySubType. See SecuritySubType (762) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegSecuritySubType
FixFieldSpec.Description: SecuritySubType of the leg instrument. See SecuritySubType (762) field for description

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllowableOneSidednessPct
FixFieldSpec.Description: The maximum percentage that execution of one side of a program trade can exceed execution of the other.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllowableOneSidednessValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: The maximum amount that execution of one side of a program trade can exceed execution of the other.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllowableOneSidednessCurr
FixFieldSpec.Description: The currency that AllowableOneSidednessValue (766) is expressed in if AllowableOneSidednessValue is used.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoTrdRegTimestamps
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of TrdRegTimestamp (769) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: TrdRegTimestamp
FixFieldSpec.Description: Traded / Regulatory timestamp value. Use to store time information required by government regulators or self regulatory organizations (such as an exchange or clearing house).

FixFieldSpec.Name: TrdRegTimestampType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Traded / Regulatory timestamp type. Valid values: 1 = Execution Time 2 = Time In 3 = Time Out 4 = Broker Receipt 5 = Broker Execution Note of Applicability: values are required in US futures markets by the CFTC to support computerized trade reconstruction. (see Volume 1: "Glossary" for value definitions)

FixFieldSpec.Name: TrdRegTimestampOrigin
FixFieldSpec.Description: Text which identifies the "origin" (i.e. system which was used to generate the time stamp) for the Traded / Regulatory timestamp value.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ConfirmRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier to be used with ConfirmTransType (666) = Replace or Cancel

FixFieldSpec.Name: ConfirmType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the type of Confirmation message being sent. Valid values: 1 = Status 2 = Confirmation 3 = Confirmation Request Rejected (reason can be stated in Text field)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ConfirmRejReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the reason for rejecting a Confirmation. Valid values: 1 = Mismatched account 2 = Missing settlement instructions 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: BookingType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Method for booking out this order. Used when notifying a broker that an order to be settled by that broker is to be booked out as an OTC derivative (e.g. CFD or similar). Valid values: 0 = Regular booking 1 = CFD (Contract For Difference) 2 = Total return swap

FixFieldSpec.Name: IndividualAllocRejCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identified reason for rejecting an individual AllocAccount (79) detail. Same values as AllocRejCode (88)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstMsgID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for Settlement Instruction message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoSettlInst
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of settlement instructions within repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastUpdateTime
FixFieldSpec.Description: Timestamp of last update to data item (or creation if no updates made since creation).

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocSettlInstType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate whether settlement instructions are provided on an allocation instruction message, and if not, how they are to be derived. Valid values: 0 = use default instructions 1 = derive from parameters provided 2 = full details provided 3 = SSI db ids provided 4 = phone for instructions

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoSettlPartyIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of SettlPartyID (782), SettlPartyIDSource (783), and SettlPartyRole (784) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlPartyID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyID value within a settlement parties component. Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlPartyIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyIDSource value within a settlement parties component. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlPartyRole
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyRole value within a settlement parties component. Same values as PartyRole (452)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlPartySubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartySubID value within a settlement parties component. Same values as PartySubID (523)

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlPartySubIDType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of SettlPartySubID (785) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DlvyInstType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to indicate whether a delivery instruction is used for securities or cash settlement. Valid values: S = securities C = cash

FixFieldSpec.Name: TerminationType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of financing termination. Valid values: 1 = Overnight 2 = Term 3 = Flexible 4 = Open

FixFieldSpec.Name: NextExpectedMsgSeqNum
FixFieldSpec.Description: Next expected MsgSeqNum value to be received.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrdStatusReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Can be used to uniquely identify a specific Order Status Request message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique ID of settlement instruction request message

FixFieldSpec.Name: SettlInstReqRejCode
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies reason for rejection (of a settlement instruction request message). Valid values: 0 = unable to process request (e.g. database unavailable) 1 = unknown account 2 = no matching settlement instructions found 99 = other

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecondaryAllocID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Secondary allocation identifier. FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocReportType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Describes the specific type or purpose of an Allocation Report message Valid values: 3 = Sellside Calculated Using Preliminary (includes MiscFees and NetMoney) 4 = Sellside Calculated Without Preliminary (sent unsolicited by sellside, includes MiscFees and NetMoney) 5 = Warehouse recap\ 8 = Request to Intermediary

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocReportRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType (71) = Replace or Cancel

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocCancReplaceReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason for cancelling or replacing an Allocation Instruction or Allocation Report message Valid values: 1 = Original details incomplete/incorrect2 = Change in underlying order details99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: CopyMsgIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether or not this message is a drop copy of another message.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocAccountType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of account associated with a confirmation or other trade-level message Valid values: 1 = Account is carried on customer Side of Books 2 = Account is carried on non-Customer Side of books 3 = House Trader 4 = Floor Trader 6 = Account is carried on non-customer side of books and is cross margined 7 = Account is house trader and is cross margined 8 = Joint Backoffice Account (JBO)

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderAvgPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Average price for a specific order

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderBookingQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity of the order that is being booked out as part of an Allocation Instruction or Allocation Report message

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoSettlPartySubIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of SettlPartySubID (785) and SettlPartySubIDType (786) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoPartySubIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of PartySubID (523)and PartySubIDType (803) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: PartySubIDType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of PartySubID (523) value Example values: 1 = Firm 2 = Person 3 = System 4 = Application 5 = Full legal name of firm 6 = Postal address (inclusive of street address, location, and postal code) 7 = Phone number 8 = Email address 9 = Contact name 10 = Securities account number (for settlement instructions) 11 = Registration number (for settlement instructions and confirmations) 12 = Registered address (for confirmation purposes) 13 = Regulatory status (for confirmation purposes) 14 = Registration name (for settlement instructions) 15 = Cash account number (for settlement instructions) 16 = BIC 17 = CSD participant/member code (e.g. Euroclear, DTC, CREST or Kassenverein number) 18 = Registered address 19 = Fund/account name 20 = Telex number 21 = Fax number 22 = Securities account name 23 = Cash account name 24 = Department 25 = Location / Desk 26 = Position Account Type 4000+ = Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user defined values

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoNestedPartySubIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of NestedPartySubID (545) and NestedPartySubIDType (805) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: NestedPartySubIDType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of NestedPartySubID (545) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoNested2PartySubIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Nested2PartySubID (760) and Nested2PartySubIDType (807) entries. Second instance of <NestedParties>.

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested2PartySubIDType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Nested2PartySubID (760) value. Second instance of <NestedParties>. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocIntermedReqType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Response to allocation to be communicated to a counterparty through an intermediary, i.e. clearing house. FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Underlying price associate with a derivative instrument.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PriceDelta
FixFieldSpec.Description: Delta calculated from theoretical price

FixFieldSpec.Description: Current number of application messages that were queued at the time that the message was created by the counterparty.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ApplQueueAction
FixFieldSpec.Description: Action to take to resolve an application message queue (backlog). Valid values: 0 = No action taken 1 = Queue flushed 2 = Overlay last 3 = End session

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoAltMDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of alternative market data sources

FixFieldSpec.Name: AltMDSourceID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Session layer source for market data (For the standard FIX session layer, this would be the TargetCompID (56) where market data can be obtained).

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecondaryTradeReportID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Secondary trade report identifier - can be used to associate an additional identifier with a trade.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderInputDevice

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingTradingSessionID

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingTradingSessionSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Trading Session sub identifier in which the underlying instrument trades

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeLegRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reference to the leg of a multileg instrument to which this trade refers

FixFieldSpec.Name: ExpirationCycle
FixFieldSpec.Description: Part of trading cycle when an instrument expires. Field is applicable for derivatives. Valid values: 0 = Expire on trading session close (default) 1 = Expire on trading session open

FixFieldSpec.Name: TrdType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Trade: Valid values: 0 = Regular Trade 1 = Block Trade 2 = EFP (Exchange for Physical) 3 = Transfer 4 = Late Trade 5 = T Trade 6 = Weighted Average Price Trade 7 = Bunched Trade 8 = Late Bunched Trade 9 =Prior Reference Price Trade 10 = After Hours Trade

FixFieldSpec.Name: TrdSubType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Further qualification to the trade type

FixFieldSpec.Name: TransferReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason trade is being transferred

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNumAssignmentReports
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total Number of Assignment Reports being returned to a firm

FixFieldSpec.Name: AsgnRptID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for the Assignment Report

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegMoveType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Describes whether peg is static or floats Valid Values 0 = Floating (default) 1 = Fixed

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegOffsetType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Peg Offset value Valid Values 0 = Price (default) 1 = Basis Points 2 = Ticks 3 = Price Tier / Level

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegLimitType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Peg Limit Valid Values 0 = Or better (default) - price improvement allowed 1 = Strict – limit is a strict limit 2 = Or worse – for a buy the peg limit is a minimum and for a sell the peg limit is a maximum (for use for orders which have a price range)

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegRoundDirection
FixFieldSpec.Description: If the calculated peg price is not a valid tick price, specifies whether to round the price to be more or less aggressive Valid Values 1 = More aggressive – on a buy order round the price up round up to the nearest tick, on a sell round down to the nearest tick 2 = More passive – on a buy order round down to nearest tick on a sell order round up to nearest tick

FixFieldSpec.Name: PeggedPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: The price the order is currently pegged at

FixFieldSpec.Name: PegScope
FixFieldSpec.Description: The scope of the peg Valid values: 1 = Local (Exchange, ECN, ATS) 2 = National 3 = Global 4 = National excluding local

FixFieldSpec.Name: DiscretionMoveType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Describes whether discretionay price is static or floats Valid Values 0 = Floating (default) 1 = Fixed

FixFieldSpec.Name: DiscretionOffsetType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Discretion Offset value Valid Values 0 = Price (default) 1 = Basis Points 2 = Ticks 3 = Price Tier / Level

FixFieldSpec.Name: DiscretionLimitType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Discretion Limit Valid Values 0 = Or better (default) - price improvement allowed 1 = Strict – limit is a strict limit 2 = Or worse – for a buy the discretion price is a minimum and for a sell the discretion price is a maximum (for use for orders which have a price range)

FixFieldSpec.Name: DiscretionRoundDirection
FixFieldSpec.Description: If the calculated discretionary price is not a valid tick price, specifies whether to round the price to be more or less aggressive Valid Values 1 = More aggressive – on a buy order round the price up round up to the nearest tick, on a sell round down to the nearest tick 2 = More passive – on a buy order round down to nearest tick on a sell order round up to nearest tick

FixFieldSpec.Name: DiscretionPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: The current discretionary price of the order

FixFieldSpec.Name: DiscretionScope
FixFieldSpec.Description: The scope of the discretion Valid values: 1 = Local (Exchange, ECN, ATS) 2 = National 3 = Global 4 = National excluding local

FixFieldSpec.Name: TargetStrategy
FixFieldSpec.Description: The target strategy of the order Example Values 1 = VWAP 2 = Participate (i.e. aim to be x percent of the market volume) 3 = Mininize market impact 1000+ = Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user defined values

FixFieldSpec.Name: TargetStrategyParameters
FixFieldSpec.Description: Field to allow further specification of the TargetStrategy – usage to be agreed between counterparties

FixFieldSpec.Name: ParticipationRate
FixFieldSpec.Description: For a TargetStrategy=Participate order specifies the target particpation rate. For other order types this is a volume limit (i.e. do not be more than this percent of the market volume)

FixFieldSpec.Name: TargetStrategyPerformance
FixFieldSpec.Description: For communication of the performance of the order versus the target strategy

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastLiquidityInd
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicator to identify whether this fill was a result of a liquidity provider providing or liquidity taker taking the liquidity. Applicable only for OrdStatus of Partial or Filled. Valid values: 1 = Added Liquidity 2 = Removed Liquidity 3 = Liquidity Routed Out

FixFieldSpec.Name: PublishTrdIndicator
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates if a trade should be reported via a market reporting service. Valid values: Y = Report trade N = Do not report trade

FixFieldSpec.Name: ShortSaleReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason for short sale. Valid values: 0 = Dealer Sold Short 1 = Dealer Sold Short Exempt 2 = Selling Customer Sold Short 3 = Selling Customer Sold Short Exempt 4 = Qualifed Service Representative (QSR) or Automatic Giveup (AGU) Contra Side Sold Short 5 = QSR or AGU Contra Side Sold Short Exempt

FixFieldSpec.Name: QtyType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of quantity specified in a quantity field: Valid values: 0 = Units (shares, par, currency) 1 = Contracts (if used - should specify ContractMultiplier (tag 231))

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecondaryTrdType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Additional TrdType (see tag 828) assigned to a trade by trade match system.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TradeReportType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of Trade Report Valid values: 0 = Submit 1 = Alleged 2 = Accept 3 = Decline 4 = Addendum 5 = No/Was 6 = Trade Report Cancel 7 = Locked In Trade Break

FixFieldSpec.Name: AllocNoOrdersType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates how the orders being booked and allocated by an Allocation Instruction or Allocation Report message are identified, i.e. by explicit definition in the NoOrders group or not. Value values: 0 = Not specified 1 = Explicit list provided

FixFieldSpec.Name: SharedCommission
FixFieldSpec.Description: Commission to be shared with a third party, e.g. as part of a directed brokerage commission sharing arrangement.

FixFieldSpec.Name: ConfirmReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a Confirmation Request message

FixFieldSpec.Name: AvgParPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to express average price as percent of par (used where AvgPx field is expressed in some other way)

FixFieldSpec.Name: ReportedPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reported price (used to differentiate from AvgPx on a confirmation of a marked-up or marked-down principal trade)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoCapacities
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of repeating OrderCapacity entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: OrderCapacityQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Quantity executed under a specific OrderCapacity (e.g. quantity executed as agent, quantity executed as principal)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoEvents
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of repeating EventType entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EventType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the type of event Valid values: 1 = Put 2 = Call 3 = Tender 4 = Sinking Fund Call 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: EventDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Date of event

FixFieldSpec.Name: EventPx
FixFieldSpec.Description: Predetermined price of issue at event, if applicable

FixFieldSpec.Name: EventText
FixFieldSpec.Description: Comments related to the event.

FixFieldSpec.Name: PctAtRisk
FixFieldSpec.Description: Percent at risk due to lowest possible call.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoInstrAttrib
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of repeating InstrAttribType entries.

FixFieldSpec.Name: InstrAttribType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Code to represent the type of instrument attribute Valid values: 1 = Flat (securities pay interest on a current basis but are traded without interest) 2 = Zero coupon 3 = Interest bearing (for Euro commercial paper when not issued at discount) 4 = No periodic payments 5 = Variable rate 6 = Less fee for put 7 = Stepped coupon 8 = Coupon period (if not semi-annual). Supply redemption date in the InstrAttribValue (872) field 9 = When [and if] issued 10 = Original issue discount 11 = Callable, puttable 12 = Escrowed to Maturity 13 = Escrowed to redemption date – callable. Supply redemption date in the InstrAttribValue (872) field 14 = Prerefunded 15 = In default 16 = Unrated 17 = Taxable 18 = Indexed 19 = Subject to Alternative Minimum Tax 20 = Original issue discount price. Supply price in the InstrAttribValue (872) field 21 = Callable below maturity value 22 = Callable without notice by mail to holder unless registered 99 = Text. Supply the text of the attribute or disclaimer in the InstrAttribValue (872) field

FixFieldSpec.Name: InstrAttribValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Attribute value appropriate to the InstrAttribType (871) field.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DatedDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: The effective date of a new securities issue determined by its underwriters. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Interest Accrual Date

FixFieldSpec.Name: InterestAccrualDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Dated Date

FixFieldSpec.Name: CPProgram
FixFieldSpec.Description: The program under which a commercial paper is issued Valid values: 1 = 3(a)(3) 2 = 4(2) 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: CPRegType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The registration type of a commercial paper issuance

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingCPProgram
FixFieldSpec.Description: The program under which the underlying commercial paper is issued

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingCPRegType
FixFieldSpec.Description: The registration type of the underlying commercial paper issuance

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingQty
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unit amount of the underlying security (par, shares, currency, etc.)

FixFieldSpec.Name: TrdMatchID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifier assigned to a trade by a matching system.

FixFieldSpec.Name: SecondaryTradeReportRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Used to refer to a previous SecondaryTradeReportRefID when amending the transaction (cancel, replace, release, or reversal).

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingDirtyPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket. “Dirty” means it includes accrued interest

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingEndPrice
FixFieldSpec.Description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket at the end of the agreement.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingStartValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the start of the agreement

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingCurrentValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency value currently attributed to this collateral

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingEndValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the end of the agreement

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoUnderlyingStips
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of underlying stipulation entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingStipType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Type of stipulation. Same values as StipulationType (233)

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingStipValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Value of stipulation. Same values as StipulationValue (234)

FixFieldSpec.Name: MaturityNetMoney
FixFieldSpec.Description: Net Money at maturity if Zero Coupon and maturity value is different from par value

FixFieldSpec.Name: MiscFeeBasis
FixFieldSpec.Description: Defines the unit for a miscellaneous fee. Value values: 0 = Absolute 1 = Per unit 2 = Percentage

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNoAllocs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number of NoAlloc entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoAllocs in each message that has repeating NoAlloc entries related to the same AllocID or AllocReportID. Used to support fragmentation.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastFragment
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether this message is the last in a sequence of messages for those messages that support fragmentation, such as Allocation Instruction, Mass Quote, Security List, Derivative Security List Valid values: Y = Last message N = Not last message

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollReqID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Request Identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollAsgnReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Reason for Collateral Assignment Value values: 0 = Initial 1 = Scheduled 2 = Time Warning 3 = Margin Deficiency 4 = Margin Excess 5 = Forward Collateral Demand 6 = Event of default 7 = Adverse tax event

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollInquiryQualifier
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral inquiry qualifiers: Value values: 0 = TradeDate 1 = GC Instrument 2 = CollateralInstrument 3 = Substitution Eligible 4 = Not Assigned 5 = Partially Assigned 6 = Fully Assigned 7 = Outstanding Trades (Today < end date)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoTrades
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of trades in repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MarginRatio
FixFieldSpec.Description: The fraction of the cash consideration that must be collateralized, expressed as a percent. A MarginRatio of 102% indicates that the value of the collateral (after deducting for "haircut") must exceed the cash consideration by 2%.

FixFieldSpec.Name: MarginExcess
FixFieldSpec.Description: Excess margin amount (deficit if value is negative)

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotalNetValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: TotalNetValue is determined as follows: At the initial collateral assignment TotalNetValue is the sum of (UnderlyingStartValue * (1-haircut)). In a collateral substitution TotalNetValue is the sum of (UnderlyingCurrentValue * (1-haircut)).

FixFieldSpec.Name: CashOutstanding
FixFieldSpec.Description: Starting consideration less repayments

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollAsgnID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Assignment Identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollAsgnTransType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Assignment Transaction Type Value values: 0 = New 1 = Replace 2 = Cancel 3 = Release 4 = Reverse

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollRespID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Response Identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollAsgnRespType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Assignment Response Type Value values: 0 = Received 1 = Accepted 2 = Declined 3 = Rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollAsgnRejectReason
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Assignment Reject Reason Value values: 0 = Unknown deal (order / trade) 1 = Unknown or invalid instrument 2 = Unauthorized transaction 3 = Insufficient collateral 4 = Invalid type of collateral 5 = Excessive substitution 99 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollAsgnRefID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Assignment Identifier to which a transaction refers

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollRptID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Report Identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollInquiryID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Inquiry Identifier

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Collateral Status Value values: 0 = Unassigned 1 = Partially Assigned 2 = Assignment Proposed 3 = Assigned (Accepted) 4 = Challenged

FixFieldSpec.Name: TotNumReports
FixFieldSpec.Description: Total number or reports returned in response to a request

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastRptRequested
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates whether this message is that last report message in response to a request, such as Order Mass Status Request. Y = Last message N = Not last message

FixFieldSpec.Name: AgreementDesc
FixFieldSpec.Description: The full name of the base standard agreement, annexes and amendments in place between the principals applicable to a financing transaction.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AgreementID
FixFieldSpec.Description: A common reference to the applicable standing agreement between the counterparties to a financing transaction.

FixFieldSpec.Name: AgreementDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: A reference to the date the underlying agreement specified by AgreementID and AgreementDesc was executed.

FixFieldSpec.Name: StartDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: Start date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the buyer pays the seller cash and takes control of the collateral

FixFieldSpec.Name: EndDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: End date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the seller reimburses the buyer and takes back control of the collateral

FixFieldSpec.Name: AgreementCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Contractual currency forming the basis of a financing agreement and associated transactions. Usually, but not always, the same as the trade currency.

FixFieldSpec.Name: DeliveryType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies type of settlement 0 = “Versus. Payment”: Deliver (if Sell) or Receive (if Buy) vs. (Against) Payment 1 = “Free”: Deliver (if Sell) or Receive (if Buy) Free 2 = Tri-Party 3 = Hold In Custody

FixFieldSpec.Name: EndAccruedInterestAmt
FixFieldSpec.Description: Accrued Interest Amount applicable to a financing transaction on the End Date.

FixFieldSpec.Name: StartCash
FixFieldSpec.Description: Starting dirty cash consideration of a financing deal, i.e. paid to the seller on the Start Date.

FixFieldSpec.Name: EndCash
FixFieldSpec.Description: Ending dirty cash consideration of a financing deal. i.e. reimbursed to the buyer on the End Date.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UserRequestID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a User Request.

FixFieldSpec.Name: UserRequestType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the action required by a User Request Message Valid values: 1 = LogOnUser 2 = LogOffUser 3 = ChangePasswordForUser 4 = Request Individual User Status

FixFieldSpec.Name: NewPassword
FixFieldSpec.Description: New Password or passphrase

FixFieldSpec.Name: UserStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the status of a user Valid values: 1 = Logged In 2 = Not Logged In 3 = User Not Recognised 4 = Password Incorrect 5 = Password Changed 6 = Other

FixFieldSpec.Name: UserStatusText
FixFieldSpec.Description: A text description associated with a user status.

FixFieldSpec.Name: StatusValue
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the status of a network connection Valid values: 1 = Connected 2 = Not connected – down expected up 3 = Not connected – down expected down 4 = In Process

FixFieldSpec.Name: StatusText
FixFieldSpec.Description: A text description associated with a network status.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefCompID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify a firm.

FixFieldSpec.Name: RefSubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific elements within a firm.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NetworkResponseID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a network response.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NetworkRequestID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Unique identifier for a network resquest.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LastNetworkResponseID
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifier of the previous Network Response message sent to a counterparty, used to allow incremental updates.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NetworkRequestType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the type and level of details required for a Network Status Request Message Valid values: 1 = Snapshot 2 = Subscribe 4 = Stop subscribing 8 = Level of detail, then NoCompID’s becomes required Boolean logic applies EG If you want to subscribe for changes to certain id’s then UserRequestType =10 (8+2), Snapshot for certain ID’s = 9 (8+1)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoCompIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of CompID entries in a repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NetworkStatusResponseType
FixFieldSpec.Description: Indicates the type of Network Response Message. Valid values: 1 = Full 2 = Incremental update

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoCollInquiryQualifier
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of CollInquiryQualifier entries in a repeating group.

FixFieldSpec.Name: TrdRptStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Trade Report Status Valid values: 0 = Accepted 1 = Rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: AffirmStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Identifies the status of the ConfirmationAck. Valid values: 1 = Received 2 = Confirm rejected, i.e. not affirmed 3 = Affirmed

FixFieldSpec.Name: UnderlyingStrikeCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency in which the strike price of an underlying instrument is denominated

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegStrikeCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency in which the strike price of a instrument leg of a multileg instrument is denominated

FixFieldSpec.Name: TimeBracket
FixFieldSpec.Description: A code that represents a time interval in which a fill or trade occurred. Required for US futures markets.

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollAction
FixFieldSpec.Description: Action proposed for an Underlying Instrument instance. Valid values: 0 = Retain 1 = Add 2 = Remove

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollInquiryStatus
FixFieldSpec.Description: Status of Collateral Inquiry Valid values: 0 = Accepted 1 = Accepted with Warnings 2 = Completed 3 = Completed with Warnings 4 = Rejected

FixFieldSpec.Name: CollInquiryResult
FixFieldSpec.Description: Result returned in response to Collateral Inquiry Valid values: 0 = Successful (Default) 1 = Invalid or unknown instrument 2 = Invalid or unknown collateral type 3 = Invalid parties 4 = Invalid Transport Type requested 5 = Invalid Destination requested 6 = No collateral found for the trade specified 7 = No collateral found for the order specified 8 = Collateral Inquiry type not supported 9 = Unauthorized for collateral inquiry 99 = Other (further information in Text (58) field) 4000+ Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user-defined values

FixFieldSpec.Name: StrikeCurrency
FixFieldSpec.Description: Currency in which the StrikePrice is denominated.

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoNested3PartyIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Nested3PartyID (949), Nested3PartyIDSource (950), and Nested3PartyRole (951) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested3PartyID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyID value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested3PartyIDSource
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyIDSource value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested3PartyRole
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartyRole value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

FixFieldSpec.Name: NoNested3PartySubIDs
FixFieldSpec.Description: Number of Nested3PartySubIDs (953) entries

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested3PartySubID
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartySubID value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

FixFieldSpec.Name: Nested3PartySubIDType
FixFieldSpec.Description: PartySubIDType value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegContractSettlMonth
FixFieldSpec.Description: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

FixFieldSpec.Name: LegInterestAccrualDate
FixFieldSpec.Description: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Dated Date
